title: Customs computers at US airports down for about 90 minutes
text: Photo: Ashley Hopkins, AP In this photo provided by Ashley Hopkins, people wait in lines at Dallas-Fort Worth Airport in Dallas, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015. U.S. Customs and Border Protection says the computer systems used to process international travelers at airports across the United States went down for about 90 minutes Wednesday evening. WASHINGTON (AP) — U.S. Customs and Border Protection said Wednesday that the computer systems used to process international travelers at airports across the United States went down for about 90 minutes Wednesday evening.
